The paper focuses on computer vision tasks and deep learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also discusses transfer learning and semi-supervised learning, which are common topics in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a meta-learning objective, which is a topic in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of unlabeled data, which is a topic in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper experiments with action recognition, which is a topic in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
